        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 12:49AM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 1248 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Midway to near San Diego to near Benavides.
Movement was southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Alice, San Diego, Benavides, Orange Grove, Midway, Alfred-South La
Paloma, San Jose, Westdale, Ben Bolt, Sandia, Palito Blanco,
Tecalote, Alice Acres, Alfred, Pernitas Point, and Lake Alice.

This includes US Highway 281 between mile markers 646 and 690.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 200 AM CDT for
south central Texas.</instruction>
